comments.body:
OK because I see the question, why are some fields redundant/duplicates? The answer is simple because we use embedded structs.
Examples from the completion [test](https://github.com/containers/podman/blob/main/cmd/podman/common/completion_test.go) :
```
type Anonymous struct {
	Hello string
	// The name should match the testStruct Name below. This is used to make
	// sure the logic uses the actual struct fields before the embedded ones.
	Name struct {
		Suffix string
		Prefix string
	}
}

testStruct := struct {
		Name string
		Age  int
		Car  *Car
		Car2 *Car
		*Anonymous
		private int
	}{}
```

Her Anonymous is embedded in the testStruct, that means it has no extra field name and therefore the Anonymous fields can be accessed directly on testStruct `.Hello` will work but you also can do `.Anonymous.Hello`

Now why should we suggest the same twice?
The problem comes when there are fields with the same name. We have `testStruct.Name` and  `testStruct.Anonymous.Name` both are fields with different information. So as a user I still need `testStruct.Anonymous.Name` if I need that specific field.

I hope that explains why we have duplicates in the suggestions.

Also sometimes we have duplicates for docker compat.
